FAILURE_WORD.FSC_DESC: SMU reports INIT state after Initialisation Phase ended

MONITORING.DESCRIPTION: Re-Init-Monitoring starts with the end of the Init-Phase (all SMUs have a cleared INIT flag in their clusterFlags register). At this point in time the monitor shall report the event as passed to the DEM (to heal an existing entry of same type). If at any later time the SMU X (X for 0, 1, 2) reports a set INIT flag in its ClusterFlags register the monitor shall report the event as failed tot he DEM to be entered without any debouncing.
MONITORING.GOOD_CHECK_DESCRIPTION: Power On/Off or Sleep/Wakeup
MONITORING.ROOTCAUSE: Correct positive failure: SMU did a reset and is going through its init phase. False positive failure: SPI communication is so heavily disturbed that the SPI message with the read ClusterFlag contents include a set INIT bit and the CRC is correct at random

DETECTION.DETECTION_SIT: normal operation

FAILURE_WORD.FSC_DESC: Ambient temperature or temperature gradient is too high

MONITORING.ADD_RB_DESCRIPTION: Each second the delta of the current and previous average is calculated and its absolute value compared against a time-dependent gradient limit. If one of both checks fails, the failure becomes active, if both checks pass (incl. a hysteresis) the failure gets healed.
MONITORING.DESCRIPTION: The temperature signal of 1 SMU is averaged over 1 second. Each second the current average is compared against an sensor individual over-temperature limit.
MONITORING.GOOD_CHECK_DESCRIPTION: Ambient temperature and temperature gradient are within limits (minus hysteresis)
MONITORING.ROOTCAUSE: Ambient temperature or temperature gradient is too high.

DETECTION.DETECTION_SIT: normal operation
